        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), literally, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "their requirements. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is what they need. But it is said of the priests in Ezekiel, “They shall not gird themselves with anything that causeth sweat: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "That which cometh out of the man defileth him.” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Again, in God’s dwelling-place, the interior or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mishkân, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the tabernacle where He abode, was of fine linen. The outer tent and coverings were of hair and skin and wool. The tabernacle where He dwells, and the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "earthly house ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "of the tabernacle, must be kept distinct, while His tabernacle “remaineth among us in the midst of our uncleanness.” (See ",
        "children": []
