    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Still less were they to expose human life to danger through carelessness. \"If thou build a new house, make a rim (maakeh) - i.e., a balustrade - to thy roof, that thou bring not blood-guiltiness upon thy house, if any one fall from it.\" The roofs of the Israelitish houses were flat, as they mostly are in the East, so that the inhabitants often lived upon them (",
        "children": []
